sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Backend as Dashboard Backend<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Thanos as Thanos Querier<br/>9092/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant NotebookCtrl as notebook-controller

    Note over User,Backend: Flow 1: User Authentication and Dashboard Access
    User->>Route: GET /<br/>HTTPS Request
    Route->>Proxy: Forward to 8443/TCP<br/>TLS Reencrypt
    Proxy->>OAuth: OAuth2 Authorization<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    OAuth-->>Proxy: Access Token<br/>JWT Bearer
    Proxy->>Backend: Forward Request<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>X-Auth-Request-User<br/>X-Auth-Request-Groups
    Backend->>Backend: Load Static Files<br/>React SPA
    Backend-->>Proxy: HTML/JS/CSS
    Proxy-->>Route: HTTPS Response
    Route-->>User: Dashboard UI

    Note over User,K8s: Flow 2: API Request to Kubernetes
    User->>Route: POST /api/notebooks<br/>Bearer Token
    Route->>Proxy: Forward 8443/TCP
    Proxy->>Backend: HTTP 8080/TCP<br/>User/Group Headers
    Backend->>K8s: Create Notebook CR<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Service Account Token
    K8s-->>Backend: Notebook Created
    Backend-->>Proxy: JSON Response
    Proxy-->>Route: HTTPS Response
    Route-->>User: Success

    Note over User,Thanos: Flow 3: Prometheus Metrics Query
    User->>Route: GET /api/prometheus/*<br/>Bearer Token
    Route->>Proxy: Forward 8443/TCP
    Proxy->>Backend: HTTP 8080/TCP
    Backend->>Thanos: Query Metrics<br/>9092/TCP HTTPS<br/>Service Account Token
    Thanos-->>Backend: Metrics Data
    Backend-->>Proxy: JSON Response
    Proxy-->>Route: HTTPS Response
    Route-->>User: Metrics Dashboard

    Note over Backend,NotebookCtrl: Flow 4: Notebook Creation (Backend)
    Backend->>K8s: Create Notebook CR<br/>kubeflow.org/v1<br/>Service Account Token
    K8s->>NotebookCtrl: Watch Event<br/>Notebook Created
    NotebookCtrl->>K8s: Create Pod/Service<br/>For Notebook
    K8s-->>NotebookCtrl: Resources Created
    NotebookCtrl->>K8s: Update Notebook Status
    K8s-->>Backend: Watch Event<br/>Status Updated
